      "en": "🔡 PART 3 — SYLLABLE SPLITTING 🔡",
      "kind": "header"
    },
    {
      "en": "OK here's a real **superpower** for spelling. Maltese is mostly phonetic — words sound like they're spelled. So if you can chop a word into syllables, you can spell it. 🎯",
      "kind": "key"
    },
    {
      "en": "Three rules. That's all."
    },
    {
      "en": "1️⃣ Each syllable has only **one vowel**.",
      "kind": "rule"
    },
    {
      "en": "2️⃣ The second syllable starts with a **consonant**.",
      "kind": "rule"
    },
    {
      "en": "3️⃣ Two consonants in the middle? **Split between them**.",
      "kind": "rule"
    },
    {
      "en": "Watch:"
    },
